public void addRegex(java.lang.String input_regex)

Adds an individual trace line type, which consists of a regex with additional syntax. The regex must match the entire line. The additional syntax is as follows:
  • (?) -- Matches the default field regex (?:\s*(?\S+)\s*)
  • (?value) -- Specifies a value for a field, potentially with back-references which get filled.
  • (?) and (?<++name>) -- Specify context fields which are included with every type of trace.
Note that \;\; becomes ;; (this is to support the parsing of multiple regexes, described above).
